### Tailwind class naming convention
Colors are registered via `@theme inline` in `globals.css`. The utility class name matches the token name exactly:
- `--primary` → `bg-primary` / `text-primary`
- `--on-primary` → `bg-on-primary` / `text-on-primary`
- `--surface-container-high` → `bg-surface-container-high`
- `--on-surface` → `text-on-surface`
- `--on-surface-variant` → `text-on-surface-variant`
- `--on-tertiary-container` → `text-on-tertiary-container`
- etc.

**Never use HSL. Always use hex values directly from the theme JSON.**
**Never use ShadCN-style aliases like `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `text-primary-foreground` — always use the Material You `on-*` token names.**

